HEADWORD: Outfly
<hw>Out*fly"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Outflew</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Outflown</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; p. pr. & vb. n.
<conjf>Outflying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To surpass in flying; to fly
